    <h1>The Girl Who Silenced the World</h1>
    <p>
      In 1992, 12-year-old Severn Cullis-Suzuki stood in front of world leaders at the Earth Summit in Rio de Janeiro and delivered a powerful speech that left the room in silence. Representing the Environmental Children’s Organization, she passionately urged adults to take responsibility for the planet’s future.
    </p>
    <p>
